    <span><u>Subject: Field Executive Engagement for FY 2021-22</u></span>
    <span></span><br><br>
    <p>Mitr Sewa Private Limited, herein referred to as the Company, is pleased to inform you that you have been
        selected and offered self-employment opportunity as a Field Executive at the above location for delivering
        various services under banner of Mitr Sewa through the Mitr Sewak engaged by you in the area allocated by the
        Company. Your engagement as a Field Executive is based on the verification of your profile for self-employment
        opportunities as Field Executive, along with your entrepreneurial credentials. The Company shall arrange
        offline/online training for various services to be provided under banner of Mitr Sewa Kendra.
    </p>
    <p>MitrYou shall carry on the Field Executive activities in self-owned/rented premises as stated in the profile to
        supervise and monitor fixed point Mitr Sewa Kendra in the allocated area. The Mitr Sewa Kendra under your
        supervision shall comply with the norms laid down by the Company and Partner Bank. You should supervise the Mitr
        Sewak to maintain the devices and assets provided by the Company and Partner Bank in good order. The Company,
        with your assistance, shall provide necessary support (technical upkeep of machines and devices, and other
        associated infrastructure and training on operations, compliances, products & services) on demand and on
        periodic basis for uninterrupted operations at Mitr Sewa Kendra.</p>
    <p>The Service Charges / variable remunerations are intended to cover your return on investment apart from
        infrastructure cost like rent for the Office, internet charges, travel expenses, administrative expenses, mobile
        charges, etc. The service charges / variable remuneration you are entitled to will be advised to you and
        changes, if any, shall be advised from time to time. Payment of remuneration shall be remitted to your account
        as provided by you during registration. Please note that the threshold level and service charges / fee structure
        can be changed by the Company / Partner Bank without assigning any reasons or prior notice. Further, any tax and
        levies applicable to the services you provide as Field Executive of the Company shall be borne by you and the
        company shall deduct any applicable taxes at source from payments to you. </p>
    <p>Your engagement as a Field Executive by the company is on a principal-to-principal basis. You are
        free to carry on other business / occupations as stated by you in the profile. You are also free to
        carry on any other business / occupation that does not conflict with the interests of the company/ partner bank.
        As an entrepreneur, you invest time and capital of your own free will and are aware of
        the business risks involved, including possible losses. Your status is self-employed with the additional
        role of business correspondent. No work under this engagement can be transferred or assigned to
        any other person without the prior written consent of the company / partner bank.</p>
    <p>This engagement is valid for a period of 1 (one) year from the date of acceptance of this letter and
        shall be deemed to be extended beyond this period unless explicitly discontinued by either party.
        However, the engagement shall be deemed to be terminated if a) the partner bank terminated its
        relationship with the company; b) the business generation level as defined by the company / partner
        bank fall below expectations consistently without valid justifications; c) any breach on your part of
        the basic trust / terms / values of the company / partner bank; d) any misrepresentation / fraudulent
        activities on your part at any point of time.</p>
    <p>This engagement supersedes all prior agreements on the subject matter whether oral or written
        between the company and yourself. Any disputes shall be referred to the Courts at Lucknow, Uttar
        Pradesh, India.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:5%;">Kindly communicate your acceptance of the above-mentioned terms by countersigning the
